    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Devices with receptacles and distribution mechanisms for sowing seed manually over a field. These consist of a sowing tray, in metal or linen, suspended over the shoulder by one or more straps. Through an adjustable opening, the seed would pour onto a spreading disc that was made to rotate. With each movement, the seed was thrown wide before of the sower.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
